Quote: The three top snow huts, Waihi Top, Mt Edith Top and the Hat Top were kept provided with rations and blankets, which were stored in tin boxes, safe from rats and mice. Lean to-s were attached to several of the huts, all the top snow ones, for the musterers' dogs.
